  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I get an internship at IITs in December?",
  "response": "Obtaining an internship at Indian Institutes of Technology (IITs) in December involves a few strategic steps. Here are some general guidelines you can follow:\n\n1. **Research and Identify Professors or Departments:**\n   - Visit the websites of various IITs and identify the professors or departments whose research aligns with your interests.\n   - Look for recent publications or ongoing projects to understand their work better.\n\n2. **Prepare a Strong CV and Cover Letter:**\n   - Create a professional CV highlighting your academic achievements, skills, projects, and any prior internships or research work.\n   - Write a tailored cover letter for each application, explaining why you are interested in working with a particular professor or department and how you can contribute.\n\n3. **Contact Professors:**\n   - Send personalized emails to the professors you are interested in working with.\n   - Attach your CV and cover letter, and make sure your email is concise and professional.\n\n4. **Leverage Contacts and Networks:**\n   - If you have any contacts or seniors who are currently studying or have studied at IITs, reach out to them for guidance and possible recommendations.\n\n5. **Utilize Internship Portals and Platforms:**\n   - Some IITs may advertise internship opportunities on their official websites or dedicated portals. Regularly check these sources for openings.\n\n6. **Follow-Up:**\n   - If you don't receive a response within a due time, consider sending a polite follow-up email reiterating your interest.\n\n7. **Apply for Relevant Programs:**\n   - Some IITs might have specific internship programs for undergraduates. Look out for programs such as summer research fellowships or winter internships.\n   - Adhere to application deadlines and requirements for these programs.\n\n8. **Networking Events and Conferences:**\n   - Attend academic conferences and workshops where you might meet IIT faculty.\n   - Make a good impression and express your interest in their work. A direct interaction can sometimes be more fruitful than an email.\n\n9. **Online Platforms:**\n   - Use online platforms like LinkedIn to connect with IIT professors and research scholars.\n   - Follow their updates and engage with their posts if appropriate to show your genuine interest.\n\n10. **Technical Preparation:**\n    - Be prepared to demonstrate your technical skills and knowledge.\n    - Sometimes professors may ask for evidence of your work, such as coding samples or research papers.\n\nRemember, the competition for internships at IITs can be stiff, so make sure your application stands out by being thorough and professional. Good luck!",
